Thai Sister Saengpradab holds the embroidered head wear over the silk robe of Pope Francis at the Praharuthai Convent in Bangkok on Monday, in preparation for the Pope's visit. Sewing machines whir in a Bangkok convent as workers feverishly finish silk robes in brilliant gold and red, bespoke for the Pope and his entourage to Thailand this month. Photo: AFP  
